external_knowledge:
- 'top data explorers' refers to the top 3 users with the highest data access counts at each location; 
- 'places they frequent' refers to the locations where these users have accessed data;
- 'uncovered more than 10 treasures' means having accessed data more than 10 times.

sql:
SELECT user_name
FROM users
ORDER BY user_name;

external_knowledge:
- An active user is someone with a high number of access events to top locations; 
- The most frequently visited locations are determined by the number of access events; 
- Locations and users are ranked according to their access counts in descending order.
